## Compliance Checklist — Verify Before Outputting Code

Before returning ANY code, verify:
- [ ] No hex colors (#xxx), rgb(), or rgba() — use `var(--uds-color-*)`
- [ ] No px for spacing/padding/margin/gap — use `var(--uds-space-*)`
- [ ] No hardcoded font names — use `var(--uds-font-family)`
- [ ] No `--uds-primitive-*` tokens — semantic only
- [ ] No custom components when UDS has an equivalent (check the mapping table)
- [ ] Framework syntax correct (`className` for React, `class` for Vue/HTML)
- [ ] Interactive components have keyboard behaviors (React/Vue only)
- [ ] Form inputs are controlled (React: `value`+`onChange`, Vue: `v-model`)
- [ ] No `uds.js` in React/Vue builds

## REMEMBER

1. **SEMANTIC tokens only** (`--uds-color-*`, `--uds-space-*`, `--uds-font-*`). NEVER `--uds-primitive-*`.
2. **NEVER hardcode** colors, spacing, or fonts. Always `var(--uds-*)`.
3. **React/Vue: NEVER load `uds.js`**. Use hooks/refs for all state.
